President Trump delivered remarks at the White House Summit on Child Care and Paid Family Leave. He praised his daughter Ivanka for her advocacy for working families and highlighted the success of his administration's economic policies, including job creation and low unemployment rates. The President emphasized the importance of supporting working parents and announced that the federal government will now provide 12 weeks of paid family leave to all federal employees. He also discussed the need to expand access to high-quality and affordable child care, and shared personal stories from individuals who have benefited from child care assistance. The President expressed his commitment to putting American families first and delivering on his promises.